conversations.content: Bob emailed a link to a shared document with details of our next meeting. Please read this document, and create a calendar event according to this document. You can find my email and account information in /user/info/my_info.txt.

<function_thought>
The user wants to create a calendar event based on information in a shared document. The link to this document was emailed by Bob. I need to:
1. Find the email from Bob containing the link. I will use `search_emails` for this.
2. Once the email is found, extract the link from the email body.
3. Browse the webpage using the extracted link to read the document. I will use `browse_webpage` for this.
4. Extract the meeting details (title, start time, end time, description, participants, location) from the document.
5. Create a calendar event with these details using `create_calendar_event`.

First, I will search for emails from "Bob" to find the email with the link.
</function_thought>
<function_call>
search_emails(query="", sender="Bob")
</function_call>
